Market Analysis and Insights

Thin Film Coatings Market

Wide range of applications and further rising application of film coating in various industry verticals, the thin film coatings market value is projected to rocket up. Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the thin film coatings market will witness a CAGR of 2.5% for the forecast period of 2021-2028.

A thin film coating refers to a layer of materials applied on a substance or substrate to modify the transmittance and reflectance properties. Thin film coatings are deposited or applied using a wide range of techniques. A thin film coating can be used in various profiles such as the application of thin film coatings on LED displays protects it from scratches and environmental exposure. A thin film coating is thin and absorbs quickly and this results in not affecting the drug absorption. Thin film coatings are applied onto various other devices or objects due to their chemical and physical properties such as antistatic properties, adhesion properties, and prevention of corrosion.

The rise in the demand for LED displays due to technological advancements has led to the rise in demand for thin film coatings. Rising demand for thin film coatings in the automotive and semiconductor industry due to their physical and chemical attributes, the market value is set to undergo huge profits. Rapid urbanization and growth of the construction industry are also inducing the growth of thin film coatings market. Growing demand for optical coatings for micro-optical systems and sensors is also fostering the market growth rate.

On the other end, the high investment cost involved in thin film coatings will derail the market growth rate. Also, a rise in the cost of raw materials will pose another big-time challenge to the growth of thin film coatings market. Lack of research and development activities to advance the technology involved in thin film coatings will further slowdown the market growth rate.

